list.item:
These measures may consist of: 
                            (a)

Direct administration by organs of the occupation;
                            (b)

Control;
                            (c)

Supervision;
                            (d)

Observation, advice and assistance.

The purposes of the occupation are to: 
                            (a)

Ensure the security of occupying troops;
                            (b)

Ensure continuing democratic order in Germany;
                            (c)

Ensure the demilitarization of Germany;
                            (d)

Ensure the fulfillment of Germany’s treaty (vertraglichen) obligations.
